## Access Matrix

| Action | admin | attorney | paralegal | staff |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Trigger workflows | Yes | Yes | Status checks only | No |
| Search workspace | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes |
| Draft documents | Yes | Yes | Yes | No |
| View case data | Yes | Yes | Yes (assigned cases) | No |
| Modify configuration | Yes | No | No | No |
| View system status | Yes | No | No | No |

---

## Adding New Users

1. Get their Slack Member ID (profile → More → Copy member ID)
2. Add an entry to this file with their role and preferences
3. Add their ID to `dmAllowlist` in `openclaw.json`
4. Restart OpenClaw: `sudo systemctl restart openclaw`

## Removing Users

1. Remove their entry from this file
2. Remove their ID from `dmAllowlist` in `openclaw.json`
3. Restart OpenClaw: `sudo systemctl restart openclaw`
